                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>Layla has an ideal customer who has a boutique that sells trendy accessories for youth in downtown. She is noticing first-hand the trend that youth are more and more inclined not to visit stores but rather buy online.</h5>\r\n<h5>Identifying that <strong>problem</strong>, she seeks to innovate a solution.</h5>\r\n<h5>To <strong>ideate</strong>, she comes up with many possible ideas but focuses on one idea that has to do with developing a mobile app that integrates, fashion, trivia and a community.</h5>\r\n<h5>Since she is not an expert in this field she goes to one of the local universities and asks for interns that could help her come out with building a <strong>prototype</strong> of the app.</h5>\r\n<h5>She finds out the prototype can be done in a month and since the students are based in the university, they could <strong>test </strong>amongst the youth there to get feedback.</h5>\r\n<h5>Once feedback has been gathered, Layla can then continue to develop the app using the students or find a professional company to develop it after proper testing and feedback.</h5>",
