                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "<h5>“It is an immutable law in business that words are words, explanations are explanations, promises are promises-but only performance is reality.” Harold S. Geneen</h5>",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>A startup has just launched their delivery business using a very catchy name and is picking up clients at a very fast pace. As the company grows and wants to expand into another city in the country, they realize that another company has just launched a similar business with a very similar name and is using the success of the original company to get clients.</h5>\r\n<h5>As the original startup seeks legal support, they find that since they didn’t protect their name through a trademark, there is not much that they can do about stopping the copycat business. They then have to resort to coming up with a new name that they register from the beginning.</h5>",
