                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>A software company that sells office apps had a large outdoor sales team that would visit companies all day taking orders for various office apps. Some of the sales teams would take tablets to the clients to show them the products and others would take their laptops. The sales team would then come back to the office and input on the CRM tool their forecasting and sales prospects.</h5>\r\n<h5>The IT manager started to realize that as the team grows, there is a need for standardization of products so that it would be easier to manage and fix problems. it would also be important for the company to offer the ability for sales staff to input their forecasting in a simple way from anywhere and thus a cloud based solution would be optimal.</h5>",
